        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="797" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/6–2749</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-27">June 27,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>There are attached herewith in accordance with your request of June 16, copies of
                    cables covering talks held between Mr. Mark Ethridge, United States
                    Representative on the Palestine Conciliation Commission, and Israeli Prime
                    Minister David Ben Gurion.<note n="1" xml:id="d797fn1">The copies enclosed were
                        telegrams from Jerusalem, as follows: Nos. 274, 275, and 277, April 9; 291,
                        April 13; 308, April 19; and 312, April 20. All of these messages are
                        printed in this compilation, except for No. 308; regarding No. 308, see
                        footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_923">p. 923</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
